CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784249267
OL,3,CWarm weather continues as millions of
OL,4,Cdrivers to hit roads over weekend
OL,6,FThat is the second-highest since it
OL,7,Fbegan tracking the data in 2016,
OL,8,Fsurpassed only by 18.8 million in 2022
OL,9,Fwhen the easing of coronavirus
OL,10,Frestrictions sparked a surge in travel.
OL,12,FMost schools in England and Wales
OL,13,Fbreak up for the summer holidays at
OL,14,Fthe end of this week or early next
OL,15,Fweek, while the academic year has
OL,16,Falready ended in Scotland and Northern
OL,17,FIreland.
OL,19,FThe RAC predicted Saturday will be the
OL,20,Fbusiest day on the roads for getaway
OL,21,Fjourneys, with 3.8 million planned.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
