PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784249267
OL,3,CWarm weather continues as millions of
OL,4,Cdrivers to hit roads over weekend
OL,6,FThis weekend will see plenty of
OL,7,Fsunshine and dry weather, although
OL,8,Fthere may be a few isolated showers
OL,9,Fand a dip in temperatures.
OL,11,FIt is too soon to say whether the
OL,12,Fheatwave conditions will last beyond
OL,13,Fthe next 10 days and towards the end
OL,14,Fof July.
OL,16,FDavid Hayter, the Met Office's deputy
OL,17,Fchief meteorologist, said: "Every day
OL,18,Ffor the last 11 days, somewhere in the
OL,19,FUK has seen temperatures reach or
OL,20,Fexceed 30C.
OL,26,@yD@\OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784249267
OL,3,CWarm weather continues as millions of
OL,4,Cdrivers to hit roads over weekend
OL,6,F"The high pressure, which has brought
OL,7,Fthis prolonged fine spell, will
OL,8,Fcontinue for the next week or so at
OL,9,Fleast, but will shift enough to enable
OL,10,Fa more northerly flow that will
OL,11,Fintroduce a cooler feel that will end
OL,12,Fthe run of 30C days.
OL,14,F"However, we are still likely to see
OL,15,Fsome locations remain in heatwave
OL,16,Fconditions to finish the week."
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOUxD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
