OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784249267
OL,3,CWarm weather continues as millions of
OL,4,Cdrivers to hit roads over weekend
OL,6,FWhether the current heatwave continues
OL,7,Fwill depend on whether there are three
OL,8,Fdays of temperatures above 28C in
OL,9,FLondon or 25C for the rest of the
OL,10,Fcountry.
OL,12,FIt comes as Britons have so far coped
OL,13,Fwith a sweltering summer of above-
OL,14,Faverage temperatures and persistently
OL,15,Fwarm nights.
OL,17,FEngland has been particularly warm,
OL,18,Fwith mean temperatures currently 2.4C
OL,19,Fabove the average 21C that could be
OL,20,Fexpected.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
